18.2     ON TERMINATION

(a)     An employee who voluntarily terminates their employment will be provided their
                 final pay on the next regular payday.

(a) If travelling to a project within 40-56 road-driven km, ½ hour regular time pay;
           (b) If travelling to a project within 57-80 road-driven km, 1 hour regular time pay;
           (c) If travelling to a project within 81-120 road-driven km, 1 ½ hours regular time
               pay;
           (d) If travelling to a project within 121-160 road-driven km, 2 hours regular time pay;
           (e) If travelling to a project over 160 road-driven kms, then actual travel time will be
               paid at the regular rate of pay.

Travel allowance will be adjusted when the employee’s work location changes.
